SHORT FILM CASTING CALL: See You At The Funktion

Genre: Comedy/Coming of Age/Drama

LOGLINE:

A UK-based young Hungarian woman struggles to reveal that she‚Äôs moving abroad at her grandpa‚Äôs disco-themed 70th birthday party.

**Roles are voluntary, but meals and travel expenses will be covered.**

We are a University of Westminster Final Year Film Production, so we would love to hire **London-based actors.**

**Shooting Mid-Late Feb/Early March in NW London**

**PLEASE CONTACT W1990635@WESTMINSTER.AC.UK OR CAITLYN.MADELEY101@GMAIL.COM IF INTERESTED IN ANY ROLES.**

Looking to fill the following roles; some require **Hungarian** Language fluency.

items.text:
CASTING CALL ‚Äì PAID LEAD ROLE (SHORT FILM)

Hi everyone!

I‚Äôm a film student at the University of Brighton, and I‚Äôm currently casting the lead role in my graduation short film, *Interference*.

William Rayner ‚Äì male, age flexible (playing 45-60)

This is a largely internal role with minimal dialogue. We‚Äôre looking for a grounded, naturalistic performance, subtle, lived-in, and emotionally contained rather than theatrical.

The role involves acting opposite a stop-motion character, which will be added in post-production. On set, stand-ins will be used for eyeline and blocking, and performers will be fully supported throughout the process.

PAY & PRACTICALS:

Paid role (¬£100 per day, 8-hour maximum day with breaks) 

Shoot length: 4‚Äì5 days.

Shoot location: Sussex (Hastings & Lewes).

Dates: Late February / early March (flexible based on your schedule within 21 Feb ‚Äì 29 Mar).

Travel & accommodation fully covered (Airbnb provided).

PRODUCTION INFO:

This is an independent student short film produced as part of my graduation project at the University of Brighton. We plan to submit the finished film to UK and international film festivals.

If this sounds like something you‚Äôd be interested in, feel free to send us an email (interferenceshort@gmail.com), comment or DM, and I‚Äôll send over the full casting package with some more information.

Thanks so much!

Elsie Gregory ‚Äì Writer/Director

**CASTING CALL FOR TWITCH LIVE STREAM**

This casting is for talent to appear in a live Twitch stream hosted by well-known streamers. 

**Location: **TBD, Los Angeles, CA

**Pay: **$75/5hours

**Shoot Date: **Friday, 1/30, from 5 PM to 9 PM

**Looking For: **Men of all ages, races, sexualities 

**More Info:** In this Twitch live stream, our hosts will test their GAYDAR by talking with a group of men and trying to guess if they're gay or straight. The goal is to show that gay doesn't have a specific look, so we'd love to see non-stereotypical representations of what both gay and straight can look like! We are seeking men of all ages, races, and sexualities who want to showcase their fun and unique personalities!

**How to Submit:** Fill out the following Google Form

We are casting for a short comedy commercial as part of our final year for UWE Bristol Filmmaking BA course. 

This is a student production, seeking voluntary actors. The film is non-commercial and will be used for portfolio and university showcase.

Bristol-based, evening shoot on Feb 2nd.

Thanks!

**CASTING CALL ‚Äì LONDON ‚Äì THEATRE ‚Äì PROFIT SHARE**

We are casting for a new adaptation of **Sophocles‚Äô *****Antigone***, scheduled for performance in **late March / April 2026** (exact dates and venue TBC).

This is an **independent production**, developed by producer and actress **Ioanna Firaku** and co-producer and director **Una Reitere**. Due to the nature of the project, this is a **low-budget, profit-share production**, with performers paid from shared ticket-sale profits. While finances are modest, we are committed to creating a focused, rigorous, and artistically ambitious production.

**ROLES AVAILABLE**

We strongly encourage performers of **all backgrounds, ethnicities, and abilities** to apply. **Gender is not a determining factor for any role**, and all characters are open to inclusive and non-traditional casting.

All roles will involve chorus work and some devising capabilities.

**CREON / CHORUS**

*A text-heavy role.*

Newly appointed ruler of Thebes. Charismatic and authoritative, Creon believes deeply in law, order, and civic responsibility. He governs with conviction and a strong sense of duty, convinced that stability must come before personal feeling.

Rather than a villain, Creon is a leader acting from **good intentions**, whose certainty is gradually tested and fractured. As the play unfolds, moments of doubt, vulnerability, and moral conflict emerge beneath his controlled exterior. The role requires an actor capable of navigating power alongside insecurity, righteousness alongside fear, and authority alongside humanity.

Strong command of language, emotional range, and stamina for dense text are essential.

**ISMENE** / **EURYDICE / CHORUS**

Ismene: Antigone‚Äôs sister. Cautious, empathetic, and pragmatic, Ismene is torn between loyalty and fear. She represents survival, compromise, and the instinct to endure rather than resist.

Willing to move on and adapt to circumstances, Ismene‚Äôs convictions are tested when her loyalty is questioned. The role requires emotional subtlety and the ability to hold inner conflict beneath restraint.

Eurydice: Creon‚Äôs partner and Queen of Thebes. Appearing in a shorter scene towards the tragic end of the play, Eurydice carries immense emotional weight. The role demands the ability to convey grief, fear, and moral clarity through restraint, quiet strength, and a deeply grounded presence.

**HAEMON / CHORUS**

Creon‚Äôs child and Antigone‚Äôs intended. Passionate, idealistic, and emotionally conflicted, Haemon stands between generations and opposing ideologies. Courageous enough to challenge authority, they refuse to remain the dutiful child, actively confronting inherited power and breaking cycles of generational trauma.

**TEIRESIAS / GUARD / MESSENGER / CHORUS**

*A text-heavy role.*

Multiple roles requiring strong storytelling ability, versatility, and clear characterisation. **Teiresias** is the truth-bearer of the play, demanding a commanding presence and a sense of wisdom beyond human years. In contrast, the **Guard** and **Messenger** ground the world of the play in realism, offering sharp tonal shifts and, at times, moments of dark or dry humour that briefly lighten the weight of the tragedy.

**REHEARSALS & PERFORMANCE**
* Rehearsals will take place over Zoom, and in London (schedule to be confirmed collaboratively).
* Performances anticipated **late March / April 2026**.
* Venue and final dates are currently being secured.
**TO APPLY**

Please email **antigone.production2026@gmail.com** with:
* The role(s) you wish to be considered for
* A headshot **or** Spotlight link / CV

Selected applicants will be sent a short self-tape audition script.

**Audition deadline:** *08.02.2026 12am*

If you have any questions, feel free to reach out via email.

Thank you,

Ioanna

items.text:
Act 2 Performing Arts is a newly founded community organisation based in the Peak District.

We create accessible dance and drama workshops for people with various disabilities in SEND schools/groups. These sessions aim to develop the participants expression and self-confidence. 

Alongside this, we are leading musical theatre rehearsals to an amazing cast of local aspiring artists who can use the opportunity to learn new skills that will help within their future careers.

Act 2‚Äôs first production of High School Musical On Stage is taking place in March this year and I would really appreciate it if you could help us by buying tickets.

Any profits will be used to help me fund future musical performances and disability projects within the local community.

üé¨ CASTING CALL ‚Äì TikTok / Facebook Video Presenter (Manchester)

We‚Äôre looking for confident, natural on-camera presenters / actors to feature in short-form, social media-style videos, filmed on set in Manchester.

This is not traditional acting ‚Äî we want people who feel comfortable talking directly to camera in a TikTok / Facebook Reels style. Think engaging, relatable, confident, and modern.

üîπ The Role

Present short, punchy scripts straight to camera

TikTok / Facebook-style delivery (15‚Äì60 seconds)

High-energy but natural ‚Äî not cheesy or overly salesy

Filmed in a studio / set environment

üîπ Ideal For

Actors, presenters, creators, or confident personalities

Anyone comfortable being themselves on camera

People who understand short-form social video

Strong communication and screen presence

üîπ What We‚Äôre Looking For

Confident speaking to camera

Clear, engaging delivery

Able to follow a script or bullet points

Professional, reliable, and adaptable

üîπ Location

üìç Manchester ‚Äì on set

üîπ How to Apply

Please send a short video (phone-recorded is absolutely fine) showing:

You speaking directly to camera

TikTok / presenter-style delivery

30‚Äì60 seconds is perfect

Example: https://vimeo.com/1119845100/ea1fd86ea4?fl=ip&fe=ec

 

üìß Email your video to:

david.s@springbokgroup.co.uk

Include:

Your name

Age range

Location

Any relevant experience (optional)

 

Paid opportunity.

We‚Äôre reviewing submissions on a rolling basis.

FOUNDING MEMBERS WANTED: Professional Mourners | Paid Ongoing Work | Nationwide

MournMate ‚Äî the first marketplace connecting professional mourners with families and funeral homes ‚Äî is building our founding network.

The first 500 mourners to join will receive FOUNDING MEMBER status with priority visibility, early access to premium bookings, and recognition as the professionals who built this platform from the ground up.

Ideal for:
‚úì Actors seeking flexible, meaningful paid work
‚úì Musicians (vocalists, pianists, bagpipers, etc.)
‚úì Public speakers & eulogy writers
‚úì Anyone with cultural or religious ceremony experience

Compensation: $25‚Äì$300+/hr based on your skills and tier
Set your own rates and schedule
Emergency bookings pay +50% bonus
Get paid via secure direct deposit after each service

This isn't background work. This is real performance ‚Äî holding space, providing comfort, and honoring lives with dignity.

Requirements:
Pass ID verification
Own formal attire
Professional, compassionate demeanor

Sign up now before Founding Member spots fill: www.mournmate.com ‚Üí "Become a Mourner"

## **CASTING CALL: Background Talent (Non-Union)**

**Project:** *Alchemy In Venice* (Indie Feature Film)

**Location:** Venice, CA (On-location)

**Dates:** February 17th ‚Äì February 23rd, 2026

**Rate:** $50/day Stipend + Meal + Credit
**The Project**

*Alchemy In Venice* is a soulful, atmospheric indie feature capturing the vibrant and eclectic spirit of Venice Beach. We are looking for authentic locals and fresh faces to bring our world to life.
**Who We Are Looking For**
* **Adult Men & Women (21+):** All ethnicities, shapes, and styles. We want the true "Venice" vibe‚Äîartists, surfers, techies, tourists, and everyone in between.
* **Bilingual Talent:** Huge plus! (Please specify which languages you speak in your submission).
* **Availability:** Must be local to Los Angeles or able to work as a local hire in Venice.
**Submission Instructions**

Please send the following to **jcj248@gmail.com** with the subject line: **ALCH_Background_[Your Name]**
1. Two recent photos (one headshot/selfie, one full-body look).
2. Your general availability between Feb 17‚Äì23.
3. Any special skills (skating, surfing, playing an instrument, etc.).
4. Confirmation that you are non-union.
## **Perks include:**
* **Professional BTS Stills of you/your character in the scene.**
* **Invitation To The Wrap Party**
* **IMDb Credit**
* **Healthy and Sustainable Crafty **
* **Parking reimbursement (if applicable)**

LACAE Theatre and School Open House is this Saturday from 1-4 PM! Mini-workshops, an Actor's Career Mindset talk, Q&A and pizza! All free with RSVP. 

* [https://www.la-cae.org/event-list](https://www.la-cae.org/event-list) (RSVP here)

**Details: **
Event starts right at 1:00 PM and goes to 4:00 PM. We suggest that you plan on being there the full day to get the most from the programming.
* Address: 11031 Camarillo Street, North Hollywood, CA 91602
* Free Street Parking Available. Give yourself enough time to park and walk over. 
* Our entrance is on the side gate to the left of St. Matthew's Church. (Please note that we are not affiliated with the church.)
* Pizza and drinks will be provided. If you have any dietary restrictions, we suggest that you bring your own snacks. 
* Wear comfortable clothing, shoes you can move in, and bring a water bottle!

items.text:
CASTING CALL (Supporting Role)

Production: URA
Location: North of Romania (mountain region, very close to the border of Ukraine.
Shoot Window: 16‚Äì19 February (Actor required 1 day within this window)
Paid Role + Travel, Food & Accommodation Provided

Character: Popa Roman

Popa Roman is a man shaped by violence, faith, and the ghosts of his past. Once a highly skilled MI5 operative, he vanished from all records after a covert mission went catastrophically wrong. The world believes he died years ago. In truth, he retreated into the Romanian mountains, living in complete isolation at a remote monastery.

His body carries the map of his history: deep scars, old bullet wounds, and the quiet heaviness of a man who has seen too much. Despite his monastic life, he retains the sharp instincts, physical presence, and tactical intelligence of a former agent.

Roman is stoic, intimidating in silence, yet capable of profound emotional depth. His re‚Äëemergence into the world is not a return to violence, but an act of loyalty, a final debt he must repay.

Casting Requirements

‚Ä¢ British male actor, 55s to 65s 
‚Ä¢ Deep, resonant voice
‚Ä¢ Longer hair and beard preferred (or willing to adjust look)
‚Ä¢ Strong physical presence; expressive eyes
‚Ä¢ Must be able to travel to Romania for 3 days (16‚Äì19 February)
‚Ä¢ Required on set one shooting day
‚Ä¢ Experience with action, emotional drama, or military/intelligence roles is a plus

We are already 85% in production and this will be the ending scene. 
The actor has continuation and he‚Äôll play a key role in the trilogy, also he must be willing to get in a helicopter for this scene. 

Role Type

Supporting role with high emotional impact and major significance for the trilogy‚Äôs overarching narrative.

Please send a headshot and your showreel to:
romulus.hotea@urathemovie.com or DM for more details. 

More info can be found here:

sharedPost.text:
This year is the 60th anniversary of England's one and only World Cup win. The play 'You thought it was all Over' requires a full cast for a reading event before June 15th. See link for script details:
https://www.lulu.com/shop/pt-rose/you-thought-it-was-all-over/paperback/product-gj9g4ye.html?q=PT+Rose+&page=1&pageSize=4

Cast Required:
Cissie Charlton ‚Äì Mother. Fiercely loving, humble, intuitive, with a quiet authority. Dressed in a simple apron over a faded floral dress, evoking the hardy spirit of Ashington miners' wives. Her voice carries the Geordie lilt of Northumberland, warm yet unyielding.

Sir Alf Ramsey ‚Äì England manager. Formal, analytical, proud of discipline and order. Overcoat and a hat, waistcoat underneath and tie, pipe in hand, with a calm, authoritative demeanor masking quiet introspection.

Sir Matt Busby ‚Äì warm, reflective, Scottish, philosophical

Jack Charlton ‚Äì The elder son, direct, earthy, with unresolved bitterness. In his ghostly Leeds United kit, rough-hewn and boisterous, with a laugh like thunder and eyes that betray old wounds.

Bobby Charlton ‚Äì The younger son, reserved, haunted by duty and distance. Slender, elegant in Manchester United red, his movements precise, his smile tentative

George Best ‚Äì charming, mischievous, poetic

Eusebio - Portuguese GOAT

Email me if you are interested in being involved on  casting@kswnetwork.com
Reading location TBC
Please share

*MUST BE 21 YEARS OR OLDER*

DETAILS:

Project: OHIO LOTTERY Commercial

Filming Location: Columbus, OH area 

Shoot Date(s): Wednesday 2.04, Thursday 2.05 & Friday 2.06 (EXTRAS WILL ONLY WORK *ONE* OF THE DATES)

Pay Rate: $350 for the day

Kind regards,
Angela Boehm Casting Team

PLEASE NOTE: This is just a submission. If you are booked, we will reach out to YOU.

items.text:
ISO NON-UNION BACKGROUND TALENT FOR ‚Äú*PANKCAKE SKANK*,‚Äù a punk-inflected, surreal short film set in a neon, always-night world where a pancake-thieving outlaw disrupts the lives of everyone she crosses paths with.

SHOOT DATES: February 16-21st

LOCATION: Las Vegas 

We‚Äôre building a sci-fi punk universe and looking for visually striking, unconventional performers with strong character energy. Distinct physical traits, bold style, and unique presence are highly encouraged. All genders, body types, and backgrounds welcome. Queer- and LGBTQ+-friendly set.

**Featured Background (PAID):**

‚Ä¢ **Nuclear Family** ‚Äì Mom & Dad (30‚Äì40s), Daughter & Son (8‚Äì13)

*Shoots Saturday, 2/21.* Must be comfortable with special effects maple syrup on wardrobe/skin. It is a plus if you are a real family willing to work together.

‚Ä¢ **Teenage Girlfriend (18‚Äì29)** ‚Äì *Shoots 2/17 overnight, subject to change.* Must be comfortable with special effects maple syrup.

‚Ä¢ **Teenage Boyfriend (18‚Äì29)** ‚Äì *Shoots 2/17 overnight, subject to change.* Must be comfortable with special effects maple syrup.

‚Ä¢ **Child with Hair (9‚Äì13)** ‚Äì *Shoots 2/17 overnight, subject to change.* Must be comfortable with special effects maple syrup.

‚Ä¢ **Hostess (30‚Äì45)** ‚Äì Directed physical interaction, no dialogue. *Shoots 2/20, tentative.*

‚Ä¢ **Drag Queens** ‚Äì Strong presence and style encouraged. *Shoots 2/16, subject to change.*

**Background (UNPAID):**

‚Ä¢ Diner / Waffle House Patrons (Ages 18‚Äì101)

‚Ä¢ Waiter

‚Ä¢ Line Cook / Staff

‚Ä¢ LGBTQIA+ Bar Patrons

‚Ä¢ Police (25‚Äì40)

Background roles may work one or multiple days between February 16‚Äì21. Availability across these dates is important, though you are not required for all days. All performers will receive screen credit and meals during their work day.

If you‚Äôre interested, please fill out this google form: [https://forms.gle/WoGYUNZX8WGtjqJJA](https://forms.gle/WoGYUNZX8WGtjqJJA) 

If you have any questions please feel free to reach us at **[pancakeskankcasting@gmail.com](mailto:pancakeskankcasting@gmail.com)**.

Thank you!

sharedPost.text:
Liebe Produktionen, Produzenten aber auch liebe Agenturen und Filmschaffende in Deutschland:

+++ Der  erste Gagenkatalog f√ºr Kompars*innen und Kleindarsteller*innen ist seit ein paar Tagen √∂ffentlich! +++

Die darin angegebenen Betr√§ge sind Empfehlungen der Initiative Faire Gagen und beruhen auf den Erfahrungen vieler etablierter Filmschaffender und ihren R√ºckmeldungen an unsere Initiative, als auch auf Gespr√§che unsererseits mit Agenturen und Produktionen. 
 
Dabei werden auch schrittweise gew√§hlte Ziele des Katalogs (z.B. von budget-schw√§cheren Produktionen) zu mehr Fairness und damit auch wieder zu h√∂herer Motivation der Filmschaffenden f√ºhren.

Nachweislich kommt es gerade durch etablierte Filmschaffende zu weniger Problemen beim Buchungsprocedere und ganz besonders am Set, als bei st√§ndig neu gecasteten Menschen, die eben oft ganz andere Beweggr√ºnde haben, wie z.B. "einfach mal dabei sein" und dies auch selbst f√ºr eigentlich nicht mehr Faire Gagen. 

Dazu jedoch nur als Beispiel, die bekanntlich  immer h√∂her steigende Zahl von kurzfristigen Buchungs-Absagen und dabei besonders das Nichterscheinen am Drehort ohne Absage, festgebuchter Kompars*innen. 
Besonders letzteres sehen selbstverst√§ndlich auch wir als ein absolutes "No Go" gegen√ºber unseren Produktionen und Agenturen an.

+++ Eine faire Bezahlung aber auch das schrittweise Umdenken bez√ºglich veralteter Setregeln, oder kaum noch nachvollziebarer Buchungsbeschr√§nkungen (Beispiel Altersgrenzen) wird, verbunden mit  einer h√∂heren Wertsch√§tzung gegen√ºber den Filmschaffenden,  nicht nur zu  einem besseren Arbeitsklima f√ºhren, sondern zwangsl√§ufig auch ein Garant f√ºr direkte  Zeit- und Kosteneinsparungen der Produktionen sein. +++

Auch die Agenturen k√∂nnten so zumindest bei dem f√ºr jede Produktion so wichtigen Faktor "Zeit" profitieren und so noch effizienter und professioneller f√ºr ihre zu betreuenden Produktionen arbeiten.
Tats√§chlich werden nur so beide Seiten mittel- und langfristig provitieren. 
Der leider oft voreilig eingesetzte  Rotstift mancher Produktionen hat bereits viele etablierte und zuverl√§ssige Filmschaffende in den letzten  Jahren zwangsl√§ufig verprellt. 

Daher sehen wir auch ganz allgemein, dass eine Philosophie von "Einsparungen" und "Weiter so" (auf einem sich nicht mehr lohnenden Gagen-Niveau) dem deutschen Film eher schaden als n√ºtzen wird.
Produktionen, die sich eh schon an faire Gagen und Zuschl√§ge halten sind hier nat√ºrlich weniger angesprochen. Sie dienen f√ºr uns jedoch als absolut beispielhaft f√ºr alle anderen, denn sie zeigen uns schon seit vielen Jahren sehr eindrucksvoll, dass Fairness und Wertsch√§tzung eben doch ganz einfach funktioniert.

Initiative Faire Gagen.

items.text:
Actors always ask me‚Ä¶
‚ÄúWhat should I be doing daily?‚Äù

So I built a system I use with a select few actors I mentor personally.

It‚Äôs called my FOUR PILLARS:

EVALUATION ‚Äì Where am I right now? Skills, mindset, materials, energy. No ego. Just truth.
INTENTIONS ‚Äì What am I moving toward? Auditions, agents, showreel, visibility, training. Direction creates momentum.
EVALUATION (AGAIN) ‚Äì Are my actions actually matching the goal? Or am I just ‚Äúbeing busy‚Äù? This is where actors level up fast.
GRATITUDE ‚Äì Because desperation repels and confidence attracts. Gratitude keeps you grounded, abundant and sharp.

This is the difference between actors who hope‚Ä¶ and actors who build careers on purpose.

I only go this deep with a small number of actors inside my personal mentoring circle.

üëâ One place has just become available.
Serious enquiries: matt@mzacting.com

More acting tools & training:
üîó linktr.ee/mattzina

Actors always ask me‚Ä¶
‚ÄúWhat should I be doing daily?‚Äù

So I built a system I use with a select few actors I mentor personally.

It‚Äôs called my FOUR PILLARS:

EVALUATION ‚Äì Where am I right now? Skills, mindset, materials, energy. No ego. Just truth.
INTENTIONS ‚Äì What am I moving toward? Auditions, agents, showreel, visibility, training. Direction creates momentum.
EVALUATION (AGAIN) ‚Äì Are my actions actually matching the goal? Or am I just ‚Äúbeing busy‚Äù? This is where actors level up fast.
GRATITUDE ‚Äì Because desperation repels and confidence attracts. Gratitude keeps you grounded, abundant and sharp.

This is the difference between actors who hope‚Ä¶ and actors who build careers on purpose.

I only go this deep with a small number of actors inside my personal mentoring circle.

üëâ One place has just become available.
Serious enquiries: matt@mzacting.com

More acting tools & training:
üîó linktr.ee/mattzina

Mitch, an obsessive feng shui specialist who cleanses homes contaminated by negative energy, discovers an invisible stain while renovating an old house ‚Äî a stain that awakens a hidden entity each time he tries to erase it.

Grounded, observant assistant who witnesses Mitch‚Äôs psychological collapse.

üé¨ CASTING CALL ‚Äì MEN vs YN (Feature Film)

Production Title: MEN vs YN
Genre: Urban Drama / Coming-of-Age / Social Thriller
Shoot Location: Florida (or TBD)
Shoot Dates: May 2026 (Tentative)
Production Company: Toy Blackmon "Successful Toy Production"
Compensation: Credit + Copy + Pay/Deferred (Beginner-Friendly Production)
Union Status: Non-Union

MEN vs YN explores the collision between internet fame, street validation, brotherhood, and real-life consequences. We are seeking raw, authentic performers who can bring truth, vulnerability, and intensity to the screen.

LEAD ROLES

ZAY (Lead)

Age Range: 18‚Äì22
Ethnicity: Open
Build: Athletic / Stylish
Vibe: Confident, flashy, charismatic

Zay is a rising social-media star addicted to attention. Loud online, conflicted inside. He believes clout equals power until real-life pressure tests his loyalty and maturity.

Must Have:
 ‚Ä¢ Strong emotional range
 ‚Ä¢ Natural swagger
 ‚Ä¢ Ability to balance charm and vulnerability
 ‚Ä¢ Comfortable on camera & with dialogue-heavy scenes

MELO (Lead)

Age Range: 19‚Äì24
Ethnicity: Open
Build: Average / Athletic
Vibe: Calm, observant, loyal

Melo is the grounded brother of the group. He sees the danger before others do. Torn between loyalty, love, and survival, Melo carries quiet strength and emotional depth.

Must Have:
 ‚Ä¢ Subtle, powerful acting
 ‚Ä¢ Ability to portray internal conflict
 ‚Ä¢ Strong chemistry with Zay

TRIGG (Lead Supporting)

Age Range: 16‚Äì19
Ethnicity: Open
Build: Slim / Lean
Vibe: Introverted, sharp, creative

Trigg is a lost kid with talent. From stealing speakers to finding his voice on stage, his arc is about transformation through honesty and art.

Must Have:
 ‚Ä¢ Comfortable performing spoken word / rap (original or written)
 ‚Ä¢ Emotional vulnerability
 ‚Ä¢ Natural, raw presence

ANTAGONIST ROLES

REX (Supporting)

Age Range: 20‚Äì26
Ethnicity: Open
Build: Athletic / Stocky
Vibe: Aggressive, impulsive

Rex is Kilo‚Äôs enforcer. He moves emotionally, confrontational and physical when needed.

Must Have:
 ‚Ä¢ High-energy presence
 ‚Ä¢ Comfortable with confrontation scenes

SUPPORTING ROLES

KEISHA

Age Range: 18‚Äì23
Ethnicity: Open
Vibe: Smart, loving, determined

Keisha is Melo‚Äôs girlfriend. She represents escape, growth, and the future. She challenges Melo to choose life over loyalty.

Must Have:
 ‚Ä¢ Emotional realism
 ‚Ä¢ Strong dramatic scenes

TONE (Supporting)

Age Range: 20‚Äì30
Ethnicity: Open
Build: Athletic / Solid
Vibe: Loyal, observant, grounded

Tone is part of the older, wiser layer of the neighborhood. He‚Äôs not loud, not chasing clout ‚Äî he watches, listens, and represents what maturity looks like after surviving the same streets the YNs glamorize.

In the final scene, Tone‚Äôs presence reinforces that growth doesn‚Äôt come from noise, but from consistency and community.

Must Have:
 ‚Ä¢ Natural, subtle performance
 ‚Ä¢ Strong non-verbal acting
 ‚Ä¢ Ability to play calm authority
 ‚Ä¢ Comfortable in mentor-style scenes

DAY PLAYERS / EXTRAS
 ‚Ä¢ Partygoers
 ‚Ä¢ Basketball players
 ‚Ä¢ YN teens
 ‚Ä¢ Police officers
 ‚Ä¢ Barbershop customers
 ‚Ä¢ Open mic audience
 ‚Ä¢ Gas station patrons
 ‚Ä¢ Social media followers

Age Range: 16‚Äì40
Experience: None required

SUBMISSION INFO 

To Submit:
 ‚Ä¢ Name
 ‚Ä¢ Age
 ‚Ä¢ Location
 ‚Ä¢ Role Interested In
 ‚Ä¢ Headshot / Photo
 ‚Ä¢ Acting Reel (if available)
 ‚Ä¢ Social Media (optional)

www.successfultoyproduction.com Under Casting Call
Subject Line: MEN vs YN ‚Äì Role Name

üé¨ TONE NOTE FOR ACTORS

This film is not about glorifying street life ‚Äî it‚Äôs about exposing the cost of attention, loyalty, and identity in the social-media era. We are looking for truth, not stereotypes.

Liebe Produktionen, Produzenten aber auch liebe Agenturen und Filmschaffende in Deutschland:

+++ Der  erste Gagenkatalog f√ºr Kompars*innen und Kleindarsteller*innen ist seit ein paar Tagen √∂ffentlich! +++

Die darin angegebenen Betr√§ge sind Empfehlungen der Initiative Faire Gagen und beruhen auf den Erfahrungen vieler etablierter Filmschaffender und ihren R√ºckmeldungen an unsere Initiative, als auch auf Gespr√§che unsererseits mit Agenturen und Produktionen. 
 
Dabei werden auch schrittweise gew√§hlte Ziele des Katalogs (z.B. von budget-schw√§cheren Produktionen) zu mehr Fairness und damit auch wieder zu h√∂herer Motivation der Filmschaffenden f√ºhren.

Nachweislich kommt es gerade durch etablierte Filmschaffende zu weniger Problemen beim Buchungsprocedere und ganz besonders am Set, als bei st√§ndig neu gecasteten Menschen, die eben oft ganz andere Beweggr√ºnde haben, wie z.B. "einfach mal dabei sein" und dies auch selbst f√ºr eigentlich nicht mehr Faire Gagen. 

Dazu jedoch nur als Beispiel, die bekanntlich  immer h√∂her steigende Zahl von kurzfristigen Buchungs-Absagen und dabei besonders das Nichterscheinen am Drehort ohne Absage, festgebuchter Kompars*innen. 
Besonders letzteres sehen selbstverst√§ndlich auch wir als ein absolutes "No Go" gegen√ºber unseren Produktionen und Agenturen an.

+++ Eine faire Bezahlung aber auch das schrittweise Umdenken bez√ºglich veralteter Setregeln, oder kaum noch nachvollziebarer Buchungsbeschr√§nkungen (Beispiel Altersgrenzen) wird, verbunden mit  einer h√∂heren Wertsch√§tzung gegen√ºber den Filmschaffenden,  nicht nur zu  einem besseren Arbeitsklima f√ºhren, sondern zwangsl√§ufig auch ein Garant f√ºr direkte  Zeit- und Kosteneinsparungen der Produktionen sein. +++

Auch die Agenturen k√∂nnten so zumindest bei dem f√ºr jede Produktion so wichtigen Faktor "Zeit" profitieren und so noch effizienter und professioneller f√ºr ihre zu betreuenden Produktionen arbeiten.
Tats√§chlich werden nur so beide Seiten mittel- und langfristig provitieren. 
Der leider oft voreilig eingesetzte  Rotstift mancher Produktionen hat bereits viele etablierte und zuverl√§ssige Filmschaffende in den letzten  Jahren zwangsl√§ufig verprellt. 

Daher sehen wir auch ganz allgemein, dass eine Philosophie von "Einsparungen" und "Weiter so" (auf einem sich nicht mehr lohnenden Gagen-Niveau) dem deutschen Film eher schaden als n√ºtzen wird.
Produktionen, die sich eh schon an faire Gagen und Zuschl√§ge halten sind hier nat√ºrlich weniger angesprochen. Sie dienen f√ºr uns jedoch als absolut beispielhaft f√ºr alle anderen, denn sie zeigen uns schon seit vielen Jahren sehr eindrucksvoll, dass Fairness und Wertsch√§tzung eben doch ganz einfach funktioniert.

Initiative Faire Gagen.

Genre: Comedy, Web-Series (3 episodes)

Non-Union, Student Film

Audition Date: February 6

Audition Time: 9:45 AM-3:00 PM

Audition Location: 900 Auraria Parkway, Suite 439, Room 139G, Denver, CO 80204

*we are also accepting self tapes. Please email your tape by Friday, February 6, to elliot.m.harrington@gmail.com by 9:00 AM (MNT)

Shooting Dates (not all characters will be needed on all days, rides will be provided for those who need it): 
* February 20
* February 27
* March 6
* March 13
* March 20
* April 3
* April 10
* April 17
* April 24

Shooting Times: 9:30 AM-3:15 PM

Shooting Location: Auraria Campus (specific locations TBD)

Compensation: Only for Wagner and Evyn (flat rate: $300 each)

Please click on the link in the comments to sign up for an audition slot, fill out an audition form, and view the character descriptions/sides.

If you are interested in an extra and/or stunt extra, no need to sign up for a slot; just fill out the audition form!

You can audition for more than one character; however, please only sign up for one time slot. We are also accepting self-tapes at this time. 

If you have any questions, message me. Thanks again!

Call for Entries to the CITTADOR INTERNATIONAL FILM FESTIVAL!

We‚Äôre approaching our first deadline of the season, and we‚Äôre officially calling on filmmakers from around the world to submit their work to the Cittador International Film Festival (CIFF)!

This year is extra special: Cittador IFF celebrates its 5th anniversary - our first milestone ‚Äî and we would love to celebrate it together with you and your films.

Cittador IFF is dedicated to showcasing and awarding outstanding independent cinema based solely on artistic quality. Free from commercial constraints, we celebrate films that are bold, original, imaginative, and inspiring - stories that live beyond the mainstream, regardless of genre, background, age, or filmmaking experience.
Our international jury carefully evaluates every submission. Selected and award-winning films receive a public jury statement, highlighting what makes each work unique and meaningful. Award-winning films will be screened in front of an international audience in the famous CineCenter Cinema in Vienna.

We also empower filmmakers to share their voices: selected filmmakers can submit a written interview to be published in the official festival catalog ‚Äî whether award-winning or not.

Submit now via Filmfreeway, Festhome or TouJiang.

Be part of our journey. Be part of our anniversary.
Submit your film and celebrate independent cinema with CIFF!

https://cittador-iff.com

 #cittadorinternationalfilmfestival #callforentries #filmfestival #cittadoriff

message.text:
Are you an independent filmmaker ready to showcase your work on an international stage? The Cittador International Film Festival (CIFF) in Vienna celebrates inspiration, creativity, and uniqueness in cinema.

Our video ‚ÄúCITTADOR, my CITTADOR! ‚Äì Winged Words‚Äù captures the festival‚Äôs spirit and philosophy ‚Äì highlighting what makes CIFF stand out as a platform for true artistic expression.

Based on the book CITTADOR, my CITTADOR! ‚Äì Winged Words by Ana Bilic, this video reflects the core values that guide the festival‚Äôs film selection: artistic vision, originality, and emotional impact.

Submit your film today and join a global community of storytellers who think differently.

üîó Learn more & apply: https://iff.cittador.com

#cittadorfilmfestival #indiefilmfest #independentfilm #ciffvienna

items.text:
üçí **CASTING CALL: University of Westminster Graduation Short Film (LONDON)**

***CHERRY ON TOP***** ‚Äî Black & surreal comedy-drama with surrealist elements**

Shooting in London between **Feb 14 ‚Äì March 5** (exact dates TBC) 

5 consecutive shoot days

***Cherry on Top*** is a contained, actor-driven short film exploring emotional decay, morality, denial, and social performance through deadpan absurdity, surrealism, and escalating discomfort.

At a carefully orchestrated dinner party, two couples lose their manners as a wine-fuelled confession of infidelity exposes a far more destabilising secret. 

Throughout the film, a cooked duck on the dinner table slowly rots in plain view, completely ignored by the characters.

Performance style: **grounded, restrained, subtext-driven**. Think long silences, polite cruelty, sustained social tension.

**Catherine (Lead)**
Playing age: **30s‚Äì40s**
The dinner party hostess and Hugh‚Äôs wife. Elegant, intelligent, self-righteous, and controlling. Catherine has meticulously curated her life and believes she is emotionally evolved. As the evening unfolds, her composure slowly fractures, revealing unresolved issues and a quietly devious desperation beneath the polish.
A role requiring precision, stillness, restraint, and a slow, unsettling unravel.

**Hugh (Supporting)**
Playing age: **30s‚Äì40s**
Catherine‚Äôs husband. Timid, gentle, and emotionally reserved, Hugh avoids confrontation and retreats into routine and wine. Deeply likeable and sensitive, he is often overshadowed‚Äîuntil his passivity gives way to something unexpectedly dark.
Played with sincerity and understatement, allowing the absurdity to emerge naturally.

**This role includes an intense, scripted makeout scene with Ingrid. An intimacy coordinator will be present.*

**Ingrid (LEAD)**
Playing age: **30s‚Äì40s**
Alec‚Äôs wife. Obsessive, competitive, and emotionally volatile beneath a polished exterior. Preoccupied with youth, validation, and social hierarchy‚Äîespecially in comparison to Catherine. Passive-aggressive, smug, and deeply insecure.
Midway through the film, a private bathroom moment exposes her fragility as she spirals alone with her reflection.
A demanding role rooted in desperation masquerading as confidence.

**This role includes an intense, scripted makeout scene with Hugh. An intimacy coordinator will be present.*

* This is a non-paid final-year University of Westminster production. Food and transport will be provided. Credit and showreel-quality footage guaranteed. The film may be submitted to festivals.

To apply: 

Please DM or email **cherryontop.grad.film@gmail.com **with your showreel (if available) and the role(s) you‚Äôre applying for.

Open to London-based actors or those able to self-travel.

Feel free to share and thank you! üçí

I am currently Producing a brand new show for Channel 4 in creating an alternative court to resolve your disputes, without the usual costs and delays.

Has a dispute got out of hand?

Do you want to draw a line under a conflict that‚Äôs been going on too long?

In this brand-new series, from the makers of *Long Lost Family,* we‚Äôll open the doors of a fast-track court that will help people settle their civil disputes.

All those who take part will be provided with **free expert legal representation**.

**We are looking for people who would like to sort out a dispute in a swift and legally-binding hearing.**

Why should you take part?
* Do you feel that you are owed money, an apology, or simply justice on a matter?
Perhaps you want a refund on a service you paid for? Maybe you feel an ex-partner or family member has taken more than their fair share? Whatever the issue, big or small, this could be your chance to have your story heard and to reach a final verdict.
* Perhaps the civil court system feels too complex, too costly, or just takes too long.
* Perhaps you‚Äôd like the free advice of some of Britain‚Äôs top lawyers (likely in region of ¬£10,000)

**If you want to apply or have a no obligation conversation with someone to find out more then drop me a message**

items.text:
Hi everyone! My name is Ilya and I am a cinematographer based in Burbank. I have a degree in Film and TV Production and extensive experience in documentary and scripted event cinematography.

I am looking to get back into narrative filmmaking and want to collaborate with directors and screenwriters on short film projects for festivals. 

My goal is to find like-minded creative people, practice my professional English, and contribute to high-quality visual storytelling.

I am not looking to direct or write; I want to focus on my role behind the lens. However, I am looking for a true creative partnership where my input on the visual language is valued. I care deeply about the final result and want to work on projects we can all be proud of.
I have my own production-ready kit:

Camera: Sony a7SIII
Lenses: 35mm f1.4, 16-28mm f2.8, 28-70mm f2.8, 70-200mm f2.8 
Grip/Audio: DJI RS4, Mavic Air 2S, Zoom F3 (x2), DJI Mic 2 
Lighting: Aputure 60x, LED panels, stands, and tripods
I am looking for creative collaboration rather than paid work at this stage. 
You can check out my visual style here: https://vimeo.com/1085186593
If you have a solid script and need a dedicated DP with professional gear, let‚Äôs connect!

Hello, I‚Äôm a Dallas-based filmmaker
by the name Mopsly Man and I‚Äôm preparing my next narrative film and beginning the groundwork toward my first feature.

I have the full production gear and a clear creative direction. What I‚Äôm looking for now are committed collaborators ‚Äî camera, sound, lighting, production ‚Äî people who care about story, discipline, and pushing cinema forward, not just collecting credits.

This is a passion-driven project with real intention and momentum behind it. The goal is to grow together through the process and build something lasting.

If you‚Äôre serious about filmmaking and want to be part of something from the ground up, feel free to comment or reach out directly.

Below you will find a pilot short film I shot, wrote, and produced that was accepted in a Philadelphia film festival

https://youtu.be/jLY9aTxLb-A?si=xyTyqYGTL8-oXEqx

üé≠ CASTING CALL - BEHIND CLOSED DOORS üö™
A new original stage play written by Andrew Parris

APJ Productions are thrilled to announce that we are casting for Behind Closed Doors, a powerful new drama exploring domestic abuse, perception, and truth within the justice system. We are seeking committed, engaging actors to join a collaborative ensemble for a profit share production premiering summer 2026.

Synopsis: Behind Closed Doors follows the unraveling of a seemingly ordinary relationship, as moments once dismissed as private begin to surface under public scrutiny. Through shifting perspectives, fractured memories, and quiet moments of truth, the play explores love, loyalty, and the devastating consequences of what goes unseen, asking who is believed, who is protected, and what happens when silence speaks louder than words.

‚ú® Applicants are welcome to apply for multiple roles where playing age allows. ‚ú®

‚ÄºÔ∏è THIS IS A PROFIT SHARE PRODUCTION ‚ÄºÔ∏è

Performances will be filmed so Actors WILL be allowed to use the content for showreel üé• 

üì© HOW TO APPLY üì© 

Round 1: Email a headshot or professional-looking photo, the role(s) you‚Äôre applying for, and a short introduction about yourself and your experience.

üìß APJProductions2024@gmail.com

Round 2: You‚Äôll need to submit an intro video + self-tape to the email address listed above. 

Round 3: Should you be successful, you‚Äôll be invited to our in-person auditions at the Trinity Centre in Bristol.

This is a challenging, inclusive piece dealing with sensitive material handled responsibly and in collaboration with charities. If you‚Äôre looking for work with depth, urgency, and heart, we would love to hear from you. üé≠

DEADLINE FOR SUBMISSIONS: Monday 2nd March 2026 @ 5PM

APJProductions2024@gmail.com

items.text:
Auditioning for drama school can feel confusing especially if you‚Äôve already tried once and been rejected with very little feedback.

I‚Äôm Alaina, based in Surrey, and I work with actors applying to UK drama schools, particularly second- and third-time auditionees who want clarity on what panels are actually looking for and what needs changing before the next cycle.

This isn‚Äôt about doing more for the sake of it or generic coaching. It‚Äôs about understanding the system behind drama school auditions and preparing strategically.

If you‚Äôre local and navigating auditions this year (or supporting someone who is), I‚Äôm happy to answer questions or point you in the right direction.

No pressure just support.

Alaina

items.summary:
Auditioning for drama school can feel confusing especially if you‚Äôve already tried once and been rejected with very little feedback.

I‚Äôm Alaina, based in Surrey, and I work with actors applying to UK drama schools, particularly second- and third-time auditionees who want clarity on what panels are actually looking for and what needs changing before the next cycle.

This isn‚Äôt about doing more for the sake of it or generic coaching. It‚Äôs about understanding the system behind drama school auditions and preparing strategically.

If you‚Äôre local and navigating auditions this year (or supporting someone who is), I‚Äôm happy to answer questions or point you in the right direction.

No pressure just support.

Alaina
Drama School Business Network
Connect@actorsbusinessnetwork.com

Meine studentische Filmgruppe sucht Darsteller*innen f√ºr einen ca. 6-min√ºtigen Kurzfilm, der im Rahmen der T√ºbinale entsteht. Gedreht wird in der Fildergegend nahe Stuttgart. Der genaue Drehzeitraum wird noch bekannt gegeben.

**Logline:**
Als eine junge Frau beginnt, ihre Beziehung mit einem anderen Paar zu vergleichen, verliert sie den Blick f√ºr die Liebe, die direkt vor ihr steht.

**Gesuchte Rollen (alle ca. 19‚Äì25 Jahre):**

**Weibliche Hauptrolle**
Junge Frau in ihrer ersten ernsthaften Beziehung. Unsicher, emotional offen, stark von √§u√üeren Erwartungen und Vergleichen beeinflusst. Die Rolle erfordert ein sensibles Spiel innerer Konflikte und leiser emotionaler Ver√§nderungen.

**M√§nnliche Hauptrolle**
Ihr Freund. Bodenst√§ndig, ruhig und bem√ºht. Er liebt ehrlich, ger√§t aber zunehmend unter Druck, weil er den Erwartungen seiner Partnerin nicht gerecht werden kann. Subtiles, zur√ºckgenommenes Spiel ist wichtig.

**Weibliche Nebenrolle**
Junge Frau mit perfekter Au√üenwirkung. Kontrolliert und diszipliniert, privat jedoch angespannt. Die Rolle lebt vom Kontrast zwischen √§u√üerer Kontrolle und innerer Unsicherheit.

**M√§nnliche Nebenrolle**
Charismatisch, dominant, stark auf Au√üenwirkung bedacht. Kontrollierend und schnell reizbar. Muss zwischen Charme und unterschwelliger Bedrohlichkeit wechseln k√∂nnen.

Schauspielerfahrung ist willkommen, aber keine Voraussetzung. Wichtig sind Verl√§sslichkeit, Lust auf Spielen und Interesse an einem emotionalen, beziehungszentrierten Stoff.
Bei Interesse einfach eine Nachricht schreiben, dann schicken wir weitere Infos und das Drehbuch.

Hallo in die Runde!

Wir drehen unseren zweiten Kurzfilm ‚ÄúCry Sam‚Äù und suchen hierf√ºr den passenden Cast.

Insgesamt zu vergeben sind 4 Rollen, davon 

3 m√§nnliche Hauptrollen (Ben, Nick & Frank) sowie
1 m√§nnliche Nebenrolle (Pablo).

Worum geht‚Äôs im Film?
Ben und Nick sitzen in der Klemme. Sie haben den Bank√ºberfall wie geplant durchgezogen aber am vereinbarten Treffpunkt taucht niemand auf. Mit zwei Geiseln an der Backe m√ºssen sie feststellen, 
dass Geld nicht alle ihre Probleme l√∂st.

Die genauen Rollenbeschreibungen, sowie weitere Infos zu unserem Projekt findet ihr im angeh√§ngten PDF.

Voraussichtlicher Drehzeitraum ist die zweite Oktoberwoche 2026.
Drehort ist der Neckar-Odenwaldkreis.

Es handelt sich um ein No-Budget-Projekt, Verpflegung am Set ist vorhanden, leider k√∂nnen wir keine Fahrtkosten und Unterkunft zahlen.

Meldet euch gerne direkt per Nachricht oder auch per Mail an katlenafilm@gmail.com

**CASTING SHOUT-OUT ‚Äî FEATURE ARTISTS (60+)**

We‚Äôre seeking two brilliant character actors (playing age 60+) to appear as a playful ‚ÄúRomeo & Juliet‚Äù duo in the spirit of Compo & Nora Batty (Last of the Summer Wine) for a one-day scene in our Yorkshire-based feature film. This cameo will with our main cast, a handful of lines each, and plenty of cheeky northern charm.

**Details**

Roles:** ‚ÄúRomeo‚Äù & ‚ÄúJuliet‚Äù (feature artists, a few lines each)
Vibe:** Warm, witty, gently combative banter, think mismatched soulmates with decades of history, twinkle in the eye and spark in the step
Equity** rates (Feature Artist)
Shoot Window:** **Third week of February** (one day)

**To apply (ASAP):**

* Email kathryn@bad-fox.com with subject: **‚ÄúROMEO/JULIET ‚Äî YOUR NAME ‚Äî 60+‚Äù**
* Include: Spotlight link or CV, headshot(s), short reel (comedy welcome), location/postcode, availability for the **third week of February**
* Please note if you are 1 hour of Bridlington**

* We welcome submissions from all backgrounds and encourage local talent.
* Finalists may be asked for a short self-tape 

This is a joyful, good-humoured day on set, come have a laugh and steal the scene! üé¨

items.text:
PAID OPPORTUNITY
We are casting an actress (35-45 playing age) for the role of Janice in our 10-minute student short film Elvis Died for This.

Set in 1985, the Wright family are barely holding it together. When the youngest son, Mikey, accidentally blows up their neighbour's beloved guinea pig, Elvis, in a homemade science experiment, the family scrambles to cover it up. As the chaos unravels, Mikey finally tells the truth - about the guinea pig, and about how broken his family really is. His honesty forces everyone to face reality, and the Wrights finally stop pretending to be a happy family.

No prior acting experience is required, so if this is something you are interested in, please do not hesitate to apply.

Shooting dates:

7/03/2026

14/03/2026

21/03/2026

22/03/2026

Applicants must be based in or near Falmouth, or close enough to travel to and from Falmouth each shooting weekend.

To apply or for more information email - eb300109@falmouth.ac.uk

items.text:
**CASTING CALL: PROFESSOR WILLARD**

**Supporting Role | SCAD Senior Thesis Film // *****Opulence***

**March 5-8th, 2026 | Savannah, GA**

**Logline: **

When a Black woman becomes exhausted by passive-aggressive racism at her college, she finds inspiration and connection through a myth of Black angels sent by God.

**Professor Willard (Late 30‚Äôs-50‚Äôs, White, Male):** 

A public speaking professor at Grove Technical College for five years, originally from a small town in Michigan, now living in the DMV after relocating for his wife, Iyla (African American), who works in D.C. Willard is passionate, articulate, and well-meaning; he teaches with enthusiasm, mentors his students, and doesn‚Äôt tolerate disrespect, yet struggles to speak up publicly when racism and microaggressions arise. He privately supports Myra but hesitates within institutional systems. Outside of work, he enjoys quiet nights with his wife, debating over coffee (one sugar), and taking samba classes on Tuesday nights. The role explores the tension between genuine allyship and passive complicity; not a white savior.

**Contact:**

Producer | Hannah Ballard // hballard9hb@gmail.com

Director | Music Miranda // mmiran21@student.scad.edu

*Please submit a headshot and resum√© via email for more information.  *

*credit & copy of the film comp.

sharedPost.text:
Alternate Shadows performed `The Elves & The Shoemaker' today at Pip N Jim's Church, Walderslade  to a packed house - Just when we thought the house was full a couple of walk ups were squeezed in.  

The idyllic town of Sleepyville has a rude awakening when a huge department store opens threatening to put the town's small shops out of business.  Can mysterious stranger Den Dragon and his friendly elf friends save the day? Fast paced fun, lots of laughter, smiles and silliness.....It's Panto time Alternate Shadows style!

If you haven't seen the show time is running out - our next performance is at St. Lukes Church, Rochester on Saturday 7th Feb at 2.30pm. 

Tickets can be obtained from Val Gibson on 01634 319284 or via  email : [valgibson42@gmail.com](mailto:valgibson42@gmail.com)

‚òîüåû Dreaming of Summer? Us too‚Ä¶ üåû‚òî

While the weather can‚Äôt quite decide whether it‚Äôs rain, sleet, or ‚Äúabsolutely not today,‚Äù we‚Äôre already looking ahead to brighter days ‚Äî and nothing lifts the winter gloom quite like planning your next pantomime adventure.

My Big Fat Greek Cinderella is the perfect antidote to the February blues. Bursting with sunshine, silliness, and a big splash of Mediterranean magic, it brings all the warmth we‚Äôre craving right now.

It‚Äôs written with young casts in mind, packed with fun roles, bold characters, and plenty of opportunities for everyone to shine. And like all our scripts, it‚Äôs fully adaptable ‚Äî ideal for groups of every size, ability, and confidence level.

If you‚Äôre ready to swap grey skies for Greek skies (even just on stage), take a peek at the script here:
www.girlfridaypantomimes.co.uk/scripts/

Bring on the summer vibes ‚Äî we‚Äôre more than ready. üåäüíôüé≠
